{{extend 'layout.html'}}

<div id="reset_password">

    <p align="center">
            <Strong>Please register an email and password, so that you can begin taking the survery.<br>
               It does not have to a be a real email, and for your own sake, do not use a password that you commonly use.</Strong>
    </p>


{{=form.custom.begin}}

    <div id="register_main">

     <div class="form-group" id="auth_user_first_name__row">

            <strong><center><label class="control-label col-sm-3" for="auth_user_first_name" id="auth_user_first_name__label">First name:</label></strong>


        <div style="width: 300px;">
            {{=form.custom.widget.first_name}}
        </div></center>

       </div>

          <strong><center><label class="control-label col-sm-3" for="auth_user_last_name" id="auth_user_last_name__label">Last name:</label></strong>

        <div style="width: 300px;">
            {{=form.custom.widget.last_name}}
            <span class="help-block"></span>
            <span class="help-block"></span>
        </div></center>

          <strong><center><label class="control-label col-sm-3" for="auth_user_email" id="auth_user_email__label">E-mail:</label></strong>

        <div style="width: 300px;">
            {{=form.custom.widget.email}}
            <span class="help-block"></span>
            <span class="help-block"></span>
        </div></center>

            <p>
                                               <center><strong>It is a good idea to use a passphrase instead of a password.<br> For example, the passphrase "correcthorsebatterystaple"
                                                compared to Tr0ub4dor&amp3.<br> Not only is the passphrasse easier to remember, but it is actually more secure.</strong></center>
              </p>
          <strong><center><label class="control-label col-sm-3" for="auth_user_password" id="auth_user_password__label">Password:</label></strong>

        <div style="width: 300px;">
            {{=form.custom.widget.password}}
              <span class="help-block"></span>
              <span class="help-block"></span>

        </div></center>


              <strong><center><label class="control-label col-sm-3" for="auth_user_password_two" id="auth_user_password_two__label">Confirm Password:</label></strong>

        <div style="width: 300px;">
            {{=form.custom.widget.password_two}}
            <span class="help-block"></span>
            <span class="help-block"></span>
        </div></center>

    </div>

    <p>
        <Strong><Center>*Notice: while this website is generous enough to not display your password in plaintext here, it does not mean that it is not being stored in plaintext in the database.<br>
         It could aslo be stored in the database as an MD5 hash. That is almost as bad as being displayed in plaintext because MD5 can be easily cracked.<br>
         To learn more about MD5 and how hashing functions work, click here.</Strong></Center>
    </p>
</div>
